    slug: "hazrat-ibrahim-as-ki-qurbani-ka-qissa",
    description: `Hazrat Ibrahim AS ki Qurbani ka Qissa is a focused Urdu-language book that retells the story of Prophet Ibrahim's sacrifice — one of the most significant narratives in Islamic scripture. This volume concentrates exclusively on the event that forms the basis of Eid al-Adha: the moment when Allah commanded Ibrahim (peace be upon him) to sacrifice his beloved son, and the profound faith both father and son demonstrated in response to that command.\n\nThe book begins by establishing the context of Ibrahim's life leading up to this trial — his decades of patience, his supplications for a righteous child, and the miraculous birth of Ismail in his old age. It then narrates the sequence of dreams in which Ibrahim received the divine command, the honest conversation between father and son about what was being asked, and Ismail's remarkable response instructing his father to proceed. The narrative follows them to the place of sacrifice, the moment Satan attempted to deter them three times, and the ultimate divine intervention that replaced Ismail with a ram.\n\nDrawing on Quranic passages from Surah As-Saffat and authenticated hadith narrations, the book provides a detailed, emotionally resonant account that goes beyond a simple retelling. It explores the theological lessons embedded in the event: the nature of true submission to Allah, the concept of sacrifice in Islam, and the distinction between the intention to obey and the act itself. The author contextualizes the story within the broader framework of Ibrahim's prophetic mission and explains why this particular event holds such central importance in Islamic worship and tradition.\n\nWritten in clear, engaging Urdu, this book is suitable for readers of all ages. It serves as an excellent resource for families during the Eid al-Adha season, for teachers explaining the significance of Qurbani to students, and for anyone seeking to deepen their understanding of one of the most powerful demonstrations of faith in human history. The narrative style balances emotional depth with factual accuracy, making it both spiritually moving and educationally valuable.`,
    metaDescription: "Hazrat Ibrahim AS ki Qurbani ka Qissa retells the story of Prophet Ibrahim's sacrifice in Urdu with Quranic references, theological insights, and lessons of faith."
