    slug: "healing-with-the-medicine-of-the-prophet-pbuh",
    description: `Healing with the Medicine of the Prophet (PBUH) is the English translation of Ibn al-Qayyim al-Jawziyyah's celebrated Arabic work "Al-Tibb al-Nabawi," one of the most comprehensive books ever written on Prophetic medicine. Ibn al-Qayyim (691–751 AH / 1292–1350 CE), the distinguished student of Imam Ibn Taymiyyah and one of the most prolific scholars in Islamic history, devoted years of research to compiling this encyclopedic reference on natural healing methods that Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) recommended, practiced, or endorsed.\n\nThe book systematically covers a vast range of health topics, organized into clear chapters that address specific ailments, dietary recommendations, and therapeutic practices. It presents the Prophet's guidance on foods with medicinal properties — including honey, black seed, dates, olive oil, Zamzam water, and various other natural substances mentioned in hadith. Each remedy is accompanied by the relevant hadith narrations with their chains of transmission, alongside Ibn al-Qayyim's scholarly commentary on the medical reasoning behind the Prophetic recommendations. The author frequently references the works of earlier Muslim physicians such as Ibn Sina (Avicenna) and Al-Razi, bridging the gap between revealed knowledge and empirical observation.\n\nBeyond physical remedies, the book addresses the spiritual dimensions of healing, including the role of prayer, Quranic recitation, and ruqyah (spiritual healing) in treating illness. Ibn al-Qayyim presents a holistic framework in which physical health, mental wellbeing, and spiritual purity are interconnected. He discusses the Prophetic recommendations regarding sleep patterns, exercise, hygiene, and environmental factors that affect health. The translation preserves the scholarly depth of the original Arabic while making it accessible to English-speaking readers.\n\nThis imported edition maintains the high production quality associated with Darussalam publications, featuring durable binding and clear typesetting. It is an essential reference for Muslims interested in understanding the Islamic perspective on health and medicine, for students of Islamic studies, and for healthcare professionals who want to explore the rich heritage of Prophetic healing traditions alongside modern medical knowledge.`,
    metaDescription: "Healing with the Medicine of the Prophet PBUH is Ibn al-Qayyim's authoritative English translation on Prophetic medicine covering natural remedies and spiritual healing."
