    slug: "healing-with-the-medicine-of-the-prophet-pbuh-4-colour-local",
    description: `Healing with the Medicine of the Prophet (PBUH) — 4 Colour Local Edition is the Pakistani-printed edition of Ibn al-Qayyim al-Jawziyyah's renowned work on Prophetic medicine, presented with full four-color interior printing that significantly enhances the reading experience. This local edition makes the comprehensive knowledge of "Al-Tibb al-Nabawi" accessible to a wider readership through affordable local production while maintaining the scholarly content that has made this work a standard reference in Islamic health literature for centuries.\n\nIbn al-Qayyim al-Jawziyyah (1292–1350 CE), the eminent student of Imam Ibn Taymiyyah, compiled this monumental work by gathering and analyzing every authentic hadith related to health, medicine, and healing that Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) taught or practiced. The book organizes this vast body of knowledge into systematic chapters covering specific illnesses and their treatments, dietary guidance, medicinal properties of natural substances, and the spiritual dimensions of health. The four-color printing brings visual clarity to the text, improving readability and making it easier to navigate between sections, hadith references, and the author's detailed commentary.\n\nThe content covers the Prophetic recommendations for foods with healing properties — honey, black seed (kalonji), dates, olive oil, Zamzam water, and other natural remedies — each supported by authentic narrations and explained through the medical understanding of classical Muslim scholars. It also addresses the relationship between physical health and spiritual practices, including the role of dua, Quranic recitation, and ruqyah in the healing process. Ibn al-Qayyim's approach integrates revealed guidance with the medical knowledge of his time, creating a holistic health framework rooted in Islamic principles.\n\nThis local edition is particularly suited for readers in Pakistan who want a well-produced, affordable copy of this essential Islamic health reference. The four-color interior, durable binding, and clear typography make it suitable for both personal study and as a gift. It serves Islamic students, scholars, health-conscious Muslims, and anyone interested in the rich tradition of Prophetic medicine that continues to offer relevant guidance in contemporary times.`,
