    slug: "hirz-e-azam-card-cover",
    description: `Hirz e Azam (The Great Shield) in its card-cover edition is a widely used Urdu supplication booklet containing essential daily du'as (prayers) and protective invocations drawn from authentic Islamic sources. The title "Hirz e Azam" refers to the concept of spiritual protection through the recitation of specific Quranic verses and Prophetic supplications, and this compact booklet serves as a practical reference for Muslims seeking to incorporate these protective prayers into their daily routines.\n\nThe card-cover format makes this booklet exceptionally lightweight and portable, designed to be carried in a pocket, purse, or bag for easy access throughout the day. Despite its small size, it contains a comprehensive collection of du'as covering all major daily activities and occasions: waking up and sleeping, entering and leaving the home, before and after eating, traveling, visiting the sick, attending the mosque, performing ablution and prayer, and dealing with various life situations. Each supplication is presented in Arabic script alongside its Urdu translation, enabling readers to understand the meaning of what they are reciting rather than merely reading words by rote.\n\nThe supplications in this collection are sourced from the Quran and authentic hadith compilations, following the established practice of verifying the chain of transmission for every du'a included. The booklet includes the well-known morning and evening adhkar (remembrances), ayat from the Quran commonly recited for protection such as Ayat al-Kursi, the last two verses of Surah Al-Baqarah, and Surahs Al-Falaq and An-Nas. It also contains supplications for seeking forgiveness (istighfar), expressing gratitude (shukr), and asking for guidance in difficult matters (istikharah).\n\nThis card-cover edition is particularly valued for its affordability and durability. The straightforward layout allows readers to quickly find the du'a they need for any given situation. It is commonly given as a gift at Islamic events, included in school supply lists at madrasahs, and distributed during Ramadan and Hajj seasons. For Urdu-speaking Muslims of all ages who want a reliable, portable collection of daily prayers, Hirz e Azam serves as a constant spiritual companion that keeps the remembrance of Allah close at hand.`,
    metaDescription: "Hirz e Azam card cover edition is a compact Urdu supplication booklet with authentic daily du'as, morning-evening adhkar, and protective Quranic invocations."
