    slug: "hisn-ul-muslim-12x17",
    description: `Hisn ul Muslim (Fortress of the Muslim) in the 12x17 centimeter edition is a medium-format Urdu compilation of daily supplications originally authored by the Saudi scholar Sa'id bin Ali bin Wahf al-Qahtani. This edition contains approximately 267 authenticated du'as from the Quran and Sunnah, organized to follow a Muslim's complete daily routine from waking to sleeping.\n\nThe 12x17 centimeter format strikes a practical balance between readability and portability. The text is large enough for comfortable reading without eye strain, yet the book remains compact enough to sit on a nightstand, fit in a small bag, or be carried to the mosque. Each supplication is presented with the original Arabic text, its Urdu translation, and the source reference from the hadith literature. The organizational structure follows the natural flow of a Muslim's day: morning and evening remembrances, prayers for salat, supplications before and after eating, du'as for traveling, prayers for seeking forgiveness, invocations for protection from harm, and supplications for various life situations including illness, difficulty, and celebration.\n\nSa'id bin Ali al-Qahtani's compilation is distinguished by its rigorous authentication process. Every du'a included has been verified through established hadith methodology, with weak or fabricated narrations excluded. The book references the original hadith collections including Sahih al-Bukhari, Sahih Muslim, Sunan Abu Dawud, Sunan al-Tirmidhi, Sunan an-Nasa'i, and other authoritative sources. This scholarly rigor has made Hisn ul Muslim one of the most trusted dua compilations in the contemporary Muslim world, used widely in mosques, schools, and homes.\n\nThis Urdu translation maintains the accuracy and clarity of the original Arabic compilation, making the supplications accessible to Urdu-speaking readers who may not be fluent in Arabic. The translation conveys both the literal meaning and the devotional spirit of each du'a, helping readers connect with what they are reciting at a deeper level. This edition is recommended for daily personal use, for teaching children the practice of making du'a, and for anyone seeking a reliable, well-organized collection of Prophetic supplications in Urdu.`,
    metaDescription: "Hisn ul Muslim 12x17 edition offers 267 authenticated daily supplications in Urdu with Arabic text, translations, and hadith references in a portable format."
