    slug: "hisn-ul-muslim-14x21",
    description: `Hisn ul Muslim (14x21) is the larger, easy-to-read edition of the essential daily supplication collection compiled by Sa'id bin Ali bin Wahf al-Qahtani, presented in a generous 14x21 centimeter format designed for readers who prefer bigger text, shared family reading, or display on a bookstand. This edition contains the complete compilation of approximately 267 authenticated du'as covering every aspect of a Muslim's daily life.\n\nThe expanded page size allows for significantly larger Arabic script and Urdu text compared to the standard and pocket editions, making this the ideal choice for elderly readers, individuals with visual preferences for bigger fonts, and families who read du'as together. The larger format also means the book stays open more easily on a flat surface, making it convenient for use during morning and evening adhkar sessions. Each supplication appears with the original Arabic text, a clear Urdu translation, and the hadith source reference, maintaining the scholarly structure that has made Hisn ul Muslim a globally trusted dua reference.\n\nThe organizational layout follows the same comprehensive structure as all editions of this compilation, arranging supplications chronologically through a Muslim's day and by life situation. Sections include morning and evening remembrances, du'as for prayer and ablution, supplications for eating and drinking, prayers for entering and leaving the mosque and home, invocations for traveling, du'as for illness and hardship, supplications for the deceased, and prayers for various social situations. The hadith authentication status of each du'a is clearly indicated, allowing readers to distinguish between narrations classified as sahih (authentic), hasan (good), or from specific collections.\n\nThis larger edition is particularly recommended for home libraries, mosque bookshelves, and as a gift for parents and elders. The premium production quality, clear typesetting, and durable binding ensure that this reference will withstand years of daily use. For Urdu-speaking families who want a single, authoritative dua collection that everyone in the household can read comfortably, the 14x21 edition of Hisn ul Muslim is the definitive choice.`,
