    slug: "hisn-ul-muslim-pashto",
    description: `Hisn-ul-Muslim (Pashto Edition) is the Pashto translation of Sa'id bin Ali al-Qahtani's comprehensive daily supplication compilation, bringing the most widely trusted dua collection to the Pashto-speaking Muslim community. This edition contains the complete set of approximately 267 authenticated supplications from the Quran and Sunnah, translated into clear, fluent Pashto that preserves the accuracy and devotional tone of the original Arabic.\n\nSa'id bin Ali al-Qahtani's Hisn-ul-Muslim has become the standard dua reference across the Muslim world due to its rigorous hadith authentication methodology. Every du'a included in this collection has been verified through established chains of transmission, with each entry noting its source in the primary hadith collections — Sahih al-Bukhari, Sahih Muslim, the four Sunan collections, and other authoritative compilations. Weak or fabricated narrations have been systematically excluded, giving readers confidence that every supplication they recite from this book is supported by authentic evidence from the Prophetic tradition.\n\nThe Pashto translation serves the significant Pashto-speaking populations in Pakistan's Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, the tribal areas, Balochistan, and across the border in Afghanistan. The translation work maintains linguistic accuracy while using Pashto phrasing that feels natural and devotional rather than academic or stilted. Each du'a appears with the original Arabic text, the Pashto translation, and the hadith source reference. The organizational structure follows the standard Hisn-ul-Muslim format, arranging supplications by their place in a Muslim's daily life — from morning and evening adhkar through prayers for specific situations.\n\nThis edition is an essential resource for Pashto-speaking families who want a reliable dua reference in their mother tongue, for madrasahs and Islamic schools in Pashto-speaking regions where Pashto is the medium of instruction, and for scholars and teachers who deliver religious guidance in Pashto. The Darussalam production ensures quality binding and clear typography suitable for daily use. By making this standard dua compilation available in Pashto, this edition ensures that language is never a barrier to accessing authentic Prophetic supplications.`,
